<dl id="n22074d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n22" href="#n22074d">N22 (VI.B.17)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n22all.htm#n22074d"> 74(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ heart on sleeve <font face="wake">D</font></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Boucicault had tought the crowd, from the days of &ldquo;Arrah-na-Pogue&rdquo; to &ldquo;The Shaugraun&rdquo;mdash;this last of his pseudo Irish plays being produced at Drury Lane a few months after Parnell&apos;s first return to Parliamentmdash;that Irish patriots were picturesque and voluble persons, always with heart on sleeve, tears ready to spring, and voice eager for action. <small> Sir Alfred Robbins, <a name="TL5Y" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#TL5Y"><cite title="source">Parnell: The Last Five Years</cite></a> (1926) 194-195</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
